# Vue frontend context

When editing or reviewing Vue in Sig.App.Frontend:

- Use i18n for user-facing strings (t()); no hardcoded copy in template.
- Prefer stable refs for props (no inline objects in template that change every tick).
- Use semantic HTML and accessibility (labels, aria, focus in modals).
- Avoid v-if and v-for on the same element; use computed or wrapper.
- For code review requests, apply the code-review-vue skill (Vue code review agent).
